Key Match Events: Netherlands moved past Namibia in the final over in a game that shifted momentum.
All rounder Bas de Leede was adjudged the man of the match for his two wickets and his fighting 30 off 30 balls.
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia had come into the game after beating Sri Lanka and were expected to have the advantage in the tie.
Post-Match Reflections: Scott Edwards said, 'We did well in terms of front-loading the runs. We knew Namibia had some great bowlers in those conditions. It's well and truly in our hands, but for us, it's just about winning the third game.'

Bas de Leede said, 'I took a bit of experience from two days ago. Some of the guys will be bitter that I am scooping up wickets at the end! We lost wickets at bad times, and looking forward to Sri Lanka. We can learn from that as a team.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Netherlands have won back to back games against UAE and Namibia
The team will play their final outing against Sri Lanka in the group stage
The win places Netherlands at the very top of their group
